Subject: VBX to replace Excel or Word
Date: 10 May 1995 02:01:13 GMT

I have a client that has an existing application that uses VB with Excel
and Word via OLE. On an 8 MB machine it takes 52 seconds to print a
report and they would like to reduce this amount of time. Excel is used
to produce charts and Word is used, via an embedded Excel object,
to preview and print. I have reviewed the VB code and I do not see any
room for improvement. There is actually very little code involved
with operating Excel and Word. It appears that the application is
bumping up against the limits of the hardware and the operating system.

The only way that I see to reduce the time is to reduce the number of
applications running. If the subset of functions provided by Excel
and/or Word can be provided by third party controls than the overhead
of OLE could be removed. Very little of the power of these two products
are being used and the client is paying the price of memory consumption
and speed reduction.

I am looking for recommendations for third party controls that could
eliminate the need for Excel and/or Word. Basically the requirement is
to produce reports that contain text and charts with the ability to
preview and print.

Suggestions and/or recommendations appreciated


