I strongly recommend the Visual Suite deal from Visual Tools in
Lenexa, KS.

It comes with Formula 1 (an Excel 4.0 subset), Visual Writer, which is
not exactly a Word replacement, but is still a fairly decent word
processing control, First Impression, arguably the most powerful graphing
VBX available and some other good controls.

These tools are fairly large, but are significantly smaller than the
Excel/Word combination you are using now.
